The leadership of the All Progressives Congress (APC) is set to hold a meeting on Monday with members of the party elected into the 10th national assembly. In a notice on Friday, Iyiola Omisore, national secretary of the APC, said the meeting would be held at the banquet hall of the state house in the federal capital territory (FCT) at 2:00 pm. Omisore said Bola Tinubu, president-elect, and Kashim Shettima, the vice-president-elect would also be in attendance at the meeting. He said the senators-elect and house of representatives members-elect should come with their certificates of return. “This is to inform all senators-elect and members of the house of representatives-elect of the APC that they are invited to a parley with the party’s national leadership,” Omisore said. “The meeting which will be attended by the president-elect and vice-president-elect, will be held at the State House Banquet Hall, Aso Rock Villa, Abuja. “Senators/house of representatives-elect must come to the meeting with their Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) certificates of return and must come alone. “The meeting is strictly on invitation.” The agenda of the meeting is not yet known.